St. John's Upsets Ninth-Ranked Connecticut 89-72 in College Basketball

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-02-11T05:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/st-john-s-upsets-ninth-ranked-connecticut-89-72-in-college-basketball.html
Dwight Hardy scored a career-high 33
points to lead  St. John’s  University to an 89-72 win over the
University of Connecticut in a Big East college basketball game.  D.J. Kennedy added 20 points and Paris Horne had 12 for the
Red Storm, who are tied with the Huskies in the Big East at 6-5,
four games behind leader Pittsburgh (22-2, 10-1) in the 16-team
conference.  St. John’s, of Jamaica, New York, was ahead 35-31 at the
half and then extended the lead by outscoring Connecticut 54-41
in the second half at Madison Square Garden in  New York . The Red
Storm (14-9) shot 91 percent from the free throw line, hitting
20 out of 22 attempts.  Roscoe Smith was high scorer with 16 points and Kemba
Walker had 15 points for Storrs-based  Connecticut  (18-5).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  